<br>
<br>
We have been working on these rules, guide lines for awhile. <br>
<br>
Rules of Conduct:<br>
<br>
1. We are an honorable guild and expect all members to behave as such.<br>
<br>
2. Swearing in /gu is forbidden. Understandable this happens in the heat of a moment, but Repeated offenses is punishable.<br>
<br>
3. Since we are a Guild, Flying the Flag is a mark of Honor. Hence, /roleplay is acceptable due to certain class issues (port me, crack me, rez me, sow me, ect.), but /anon is discouraged. Sometimes you want to get away, but if a problem is causing you to feel the need to go /anon, please contact an Officer or GL.<br>
<br>
4. It is your responsibility to keep the guild (roster keeper<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub48.ezboard.com/ffatesforgefrm16.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">pub48.ezboard.com/ffatesforgefrm16.showMessage?topicID=2.topic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) informed of your advancement, alts, skills, ect. So your guildmates know how to help you and for you to help them.<br>
<br>
5. New Members are forbidden to ask for epic help thru normal channels like /gu or a raid channel, for the length of their probation. This does not mean you can't work on it. If you need help send a /tell.<br>
<br>
<br>
Guild Membership:<br>
<br>
1. Need to be level 55.<br>
<br>
2. Multi-guild is not acceptable. Conflict of interest.<br>
<br>
3. Need 5 members to vouch for you.<br>
<br>
4. 1 month probation for all &quot;pledges&quot;, but can be extended. During &quot;pledge&quot; you can not invite/recommend another pledge, after probation, with proper number of members vouching for, can recommend another for membership.<br>
<br>
5. Alts invited into guild will be after probation period. Alts have to be lvl 20 or above for a Guild Invite.<br>
<br>
6. No unresolved conflicts with current members.<br>
<br>
7. Pledges post their desire to join and why by answering the questionaire posted.<br>
<br>
Raid Rules:<br>
<br>
1. Raid Leader (RL) is the Raid Leader. If a problem, take it to the RL first.  If still a issue take it to a Officer. Other options are not an option.<br>
<br>
2. Loot is awarded.<br>
<br>
3. Clerics/Enchanter contact RL for dots.<br>
<br>
4. Unawarded items ie, Not no drop (ND), go to bank for later awarding or vendor trash (VT).<br>
<br>
5. Raid channel is less restrictive on what you say, but if someone thinks you are getting out of hand, cease when asked, don't continue or get abusive towards a request to cease.<br>
<br>
6. RL is busy, /tells to RL is often restricted due to this. Don't take offense to this fact.<br>
<br>
7. Raid vendor trash (VT) is to bolster our guild funds. Don't get upset if you receive none.<br>
<br>
8. Group Leader (GL) or a assigned person are the Only persons to request buffs. Multiple people requesting buffs often cause the same group getting the same buff multiple times. This is not mana or time efficient.<br>
<br>
<br>
Cilaru<br>
